===Country Music Awards (CMAA)===
The Country Music Awards (CMAA) are an annual awards ceremondy celebrating recording excellence in the Australian country music industry. It first commenced in 1973 at the [[Tamworth, New South Wales|Tamworth]] [[Country Music Awards of Australia]].

According the Country Music Association of Australia, Slim Dusty won 44 [[Golden Guitar|Golden guitar]] plus, an induction into the [[Australian Roll of Renown]]. (listed below). This is more than any other artist.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.country.com.au/awards/golden-guitar-award-winners|title=CMAA Award Winners|date=October 2019|access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://country.com.au/golden-guitars/award-winners/1970s |website=CMAA|title=Award Winners 1970s |access-date=29 March 2020 }}</ref>
